# Ductus Code Conventions

When writing or modifying code in this project:

- Use `.js` extensions in all import paths (ESM): `import { X } from './foo.js'`
- Builders use clone-on-write: every method returns a new instance, never mutates `this`
- Builders implement `Buildable<T>` with `[BUILD]()` from `packages/core/src/interfaces/builders/__internal__.ts`
- Use `isBuildable()` and `build()` from `__internal__.ts` when accepting Builder-or-Entity params
- Named exports only on interfaces and entities — no default exports
- Use `unknown` instead of `any` in new code
- Events: `event()` for durable, `signal()` for volatile, from `packages/core/src/utils/event-utils.ts`
- Schema helpers: `string()`, `number()`, `object()`, etc. from `packages/core/src/utils/schema-utils.ts`
- No comments that narrate what code does. Comments only for non-obvious intent or constraints.
- Run `pnpm exec tsc --noEmit` in packages/core after framework changes; `pnpm build` builds the framework
